The collaborators were Apple, Microsoft, Adobe and Google. Together they announced the publishing of OpenType 1.8, an update to the now ubiquitous font standard which was originally an amalgam of Apple & Microsoft’s TrueType, and Adobe’s PostScript font formats. NID10 Windows (3, 1, 1033, 10)		 • •
NID entry should be the SAME within the family.
Scheherazade is an Arabic font with a design based on traditional typefaces such as Monotype Naskh, extended to cover the full Unicode Arabic repertoire. It is named after the heroine of the classic Arabian Nights tale.
